-- Russia States Space Industry Losing Competitiveness, RIA Says
-- B y   S t e p a n   K r a v c h e n k o
-- 2012-09-27T17:14:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-27/russia-states-space-industry-losing-competitiveness-ria-says.html
Russia’s space industry may lose
it’s competitiveness in three to four years, RIA reported,
citing Space Agency Chief Vladimir Popovkin.  “We will become uncompetitive in the next three or four
years if we don’t take urgent measures,” the newswire quoted
him as saying. Popovkin also proposed employing private
companies in the industry, according to RIA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stepan Kravchenko in Moscow at 
 skravchenko@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  